section.section:
To be eligible for a loan, an applicant shall meet all of the following conditions of eligibility:
The Governor shall have declared a state of emergency because of a natural disaster making the applicant's farm eligible for aid;
The applicant must have been the one to have suffered the actual loss as a result of the natural disaster;
The applicant shall have applied for a farm loan from any agency of the federal government; and
The applicant must make application for a farmer disaster loan within six months of the time of the natural disaster.
